How to compile apache module:
apxs2 -i -c -a -n "ocfdir" mod_ocfdir.c

Add this to httpd.conf
Include /etc/apache2/ocf/*.conf

Packages that were installed:
apache2
libapache2-mod-suphp
apache2-suexec
libapache2-mod-fastcgi
libapache-mod-security
apache2-threaded-dev

Sites that were enabled:
000-default
Make sure to not enable default-ssl, otherwise the default config will override ocf config

Modules that were enabled:
a2enmod rewrite
a2enmod include
a2enmod suexec
a2enmod ssl

Cleanup:
rm /var/www/index.html

Replace suphp.conf with one in this folder

Here are configure options for apache (to build suexec). 
./configure --enable-suexec --with-suexec-caller=www-data --with-suexec-docroot=/services --with-suexec-uidmin=33 --with-suexec-gidmin=20 --with-suexec-logfile=/var/log/apache2/httpd-suexec.log --with-suexec-userdir=public_html

run make

then cd into support and you will find your binary
